KERNEL VERSION : 4.14 AND ABOVE

DISK ON FILE:-


1. Create a text file "/etc/sample.txt"

2. Insert the module

3. Use "fdisk -l /dev/dof" command for checking the partitions..

4. Use echo to write into the /dev/dof 

5. Create another text file with some data in it

6. use dd utility (i.e dd if=(input file) of=(output file)) and then open sample.txt to check data being copied	

Note: Don't keep the file open while copying

